Game Management System

Overview

The Game Management System is a web-based application that allows administrators to efficiently manage a collection of games and customers. The system provides functionality to add, update, and display games, as well as manage customer accounts.

Features

ðŸ”¹ Game Management

Add new games with details such as name, creator, year published, genre, quantity, and image URL.

Filter games by genre and sort by various attributes (quantity, year, name, etc.).

Display all available games and sold-out games.

ðŸ”¹ Customer Management

Add new customers with credentials and personal information (username, email, phone, city, country).

Display a list of all customers with their respective details.

Customer cards display the username as the primary identifier.

ðŸ”¹ User Experience

Modern and responsive UI for seamless navigation.

Theme toggle option for light/dark mode.

Interactive modal for notifications and a loading spinner for better user feedback.

Technologies Used

HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript for the front-end.

Axios for handling HTTP requests.

Google Fonts for improved typography.

Custom CSS for a clean and modern design.

